The paper focuses on the task of face beautification using GAN-based architecture and style-based synthesis. This involves various computer vision techniques such as image processing, deep learning, and computer graphics, which are all related to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the subjective perception of beauty, which is related to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of GANs and deep learning for face beautification also falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a novel framework for face beautification, which involves training a model on a dataset, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
